In the present study, out of the examined 220 diarrheic calves, 193 E. coli isolates were identified, 20 of them were ETEC K99 (10.36%), (Table 2
; Fig. 1
). Salmonella spp. were identified using PCR in nine cases (4.09); six isolates were S. enterica serovar Typhimurium and two isolates were S. enterica serovar Enteritidis whereas one isolate was not typed (Table 2 and Fig. 2, Fig. 3
). Three cases were confirmed to have mixed infection with ETEC K99 and S. enterica serovar Typhimurium.
